parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Fire in the Steering Column/Ignition Area
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical fire in the steering column/ignition area can cause a vehicle fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the steering column or dashboard
flames erupting from the ignition area
burning smell
smoke filling the passenger compartment
and the vehicle catching on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause a vehicle fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Ignition switch catching on fire
smoke coming from the ignition area
flames erupting from the ignition area
and the vehicle catching on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter solenoid clip connector can cause the vehicle to not start, resulting in inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Vehicle will not start
starter solenoid clip connector failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine stalling without warning
sometimes when driving
sometimes when stopped at a light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right front spring seat can cause the vehicle to sag, lose steering, and experience brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The right front of the vehicle sags
the vehicle pulls to the right
the brake line is damaged
the brake fluid leaks
the ABS light comes on
the vehicle makes a scraping or grinding noise
the spring and shock absorber collapse
the fender and tire rub together.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exterior rearview mirrors can cause poor visibility, making it difficult for the driver to check oncoming rear/side traffic, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The exterior mirrors fold in
the mirrors blow in towards the windows
the mirrors flop over due to wind or slipstream
the mirrors lose their ability to maintain position
the mirrors collapse when driving over 45 mph
the mirrors move out of position
the mirrors flop in towards the inside of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock can cause the doors to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to exit the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The door does not respond when trying to open it from the inside
the door is stuck and cannot be opened from the inside or outside.
